==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Toadstone
<hw>Toad"stone`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>A local name for the igneous rocks of Derbyshire,
England; -- said by some to be derived from the German <ets>todter
stein</ets>, meaning <ets>dead stone</ets>, that is, stone which
contains no ores.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Bufonite, formerly regarded as a precious stone, and
worn as a jewel. See <er>Bufonite</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Toadstool</ent>⟦br⟧
